cs.IT, cs.LG, cs.SI, cs.DS, cs.NE 

This paper deals with the decomposition of information in complex systems, which is a topic that is relevant to several subfields of computer science. The most likely category is cs.IT (Information Theory), which is concerned with the quantification, storage, and communication of information. The paper also discusses machine learning and statistical inference, which suggests that it could be classified under cs.LG (Machine Learning) as well. Additionally, the paper deals with complex systems, which could fall under cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) or cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). Finally, the paper discusses the emergence of synergistic information, which could be relevant to cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
